reviews.review_text: So delicious, with a calm, relaxed atmosphere. Every dish was delicious. We had a halibut special with risotto that was seasoned perfectly, and fish and chips that had a perfectly crisp batter and the octopus app was excellent. We had our young children with us and the staff was happy to accommodate. They dont have a kids menu, but made a small pasta dish with cheese sauce for the kids.

Came here during happy hour from 4-6pm and had a table on their patio. They have some really good prices for their food options especially the oysters! Fresh and delicious! Server was really hard to flag down though which was slightly disappointing. Would recommend paying a little more attention to the customers that are seated in the patio section as they tend to be forgotten about :)
Highest quality food and service.  Lovely venue too.  I had the Wild Pacific halibut ceviche and seared scallops from happy hour menu - so delish   .  Will come back to try the rest of the menu.

Another sure winner when dining in North Vancouver, the Fishworks is in a trendy neighborhood with ample parking nearby and a nice view down the street. Service is fast and very friendly, the menu if interesting and varied. Happy Hour oysters are 1.50 each, so we had a dozen. Fresh and delicious. My wife had the special, pan fried Halibut in a roasted red pepper sauce which was delicious, perfectly prepared. I had the Paella with prawns, mussels and clams, it was delicious. Atmosphere is cozy and warm, altogether a delightful experience. Would highly recommended.
This is a must do if you visit Vancouver and like seafood. The food, the service, and the atmosphere was 5 stars! We will definitely be returning next year!

To say that the food is superb is an understatement, dining at Fishworks is an experience. There is no other place that has a personal touch of the overall experience, starting from the on-the-house warm bread with a side of chickpea puree and even to the chocolate truffles,a complimentary treat at the end. Now to the real deal, you can literally taste the flavors of the ocean in your mouth. You can savour its freshness and a whole level of gastronomical expertise tossed in a plate. The Sockeye Salmon Wellington, the Fishworks Paella and the Scallop Risotto are my top 3 food in their menu! A must to recommend to my friends and family.

I celebrated my birthday in this place, the food was very good, the salmon wellington took the night away. The place was full despite being Monday, for a moment it is unpleasant that they are reminding you that you only have 2 hours because the next reservation arrives, this don t let you enjoy the dinner. Other than that, it was a very good experience. Fair prices, good portions, friendly staff. They should have something for birthday s celebration (complimentary cake or something)

My wife and I have been coming to Fishworks for a number of years now, the food and atmosphere have always been high quality and consistent. However, tonight we had one of THE best waitresses we have ever had (and we eat out fairly regularly). Maia served us on the patio and was thoroughly attentive, thoughtful, ultra pleasant, and genuinely gave us a can-do, my pleasure attitude. Such a rarity in todays service industry. A request to the owners of Fishworks, please do what you can to keep Maia on staff. We will most definitely be asking to be seated at her table for our future visits. Thank you Maia for a memorable evening!

Was visiting Vancouver & found this gem! The seafood tower was absolutely amazing & under priced for the amount of food & the quality. Special thanks to Tom the bartender. He was very knowledgeable & made us feel like we were regulars.

Absolutely fantastic!! My partner and I went for a romantic date, and totally plan on coming back. The service is phenomenal and so is the food! I have never shucked oysters so quickly before IN. MY. LIFE.
The food and the quality was amazing.The tiramisu and the fishworks seafood tower is a must try.
We were going to have a just quick happy hour, but we ended up paying $200. The food was so great and the servers were very friendly. I highly recommend this restaurant. The vibe is good.

Highly recommend, the food is incredible. Crab cakes were so good and tender. Little wings oysters were so fresh and delicate. Salmon carpaccio was amazing, accompanied with garlic chips, roasted capers and emoji mushrooms. Bouillabaisse was mouth watering, mussels and halibut in it were so fresh! Totally worth visiting again.

Delicious happy hour deals! My partner and I enjoyed the honey mussels, seared ahi tuna, salmon carpaccio, and a dozen oysters. Food was delicious and beautifully presented. The decore in the room was very nice as well. A great vibe for some good deals on seafood!
Great menu options that never disappoint. Really enjoyed the Salmon Wellington. The service is prompt and friendly. It can get a little loud inside at times, but overall an amazing experience!

Great location, awesome staff, and amazing food. We tried a few different items from the menu... the lobster bisque was delicious, the Salmon Wellington- the best! Lobster Mac n cheese- excellent and so much flavor... last but not least the Cod n chips, perfect! The portions are generous, the presentation is lovely,  and the price is right for the quality you get. The restaurant is beautiful and the patio seating was quaint and had a romantic feel to it... definitely a place to check out when visiting North Vancouver.
Excellent food, great value, and server Chloe was simply awesome. I had Sturgeon for the first time ever. Just wow! Food
Happy hour!!! We had oyster, crab cake, salmon carpaccio, and mussel. They are all excellent and went very well with their house wine. Also their desserts were all to die for.
Everything s great and Chloe was the best!

Really delicious. I has the free range chicken which was amazing and garlic white wine muscles for an appetizer and my fave dessert the creme brulee. I would definitely recommend this restaurant and go there again. the service was great and its a cozy yet chic space.

We absolutely love going to Fishworks! One of the best places to dine in Lonsdale. Quality food and ingredients served in style by a very friendly charming team. I would order anything on the menu with confidence that it will be delicious! Whether we re going out for a quick beer and oysters or a full meal, Fish works never disappoints. The food specials are always spectacular and well worth a try. The atmosphere is both upscale and cozy!

The oysters are so good and there is a happy hour from 4 to 6! We also tried the octopus and the clam pasta and both were also 10/10. Front of house was able to accommodate us even thought we were early to our reservation and the servers where super nice! Cant wait to visit again.
Attentive waitstaff and well seasoned, perfectly cooked food! We loved the halibut ceviche, seafood paella and seared scallops with squash tortellini

Lovely dinner out with my friends on a dark, rainy and dismal Tuesday evening .three of us shared salmon pate and we each ordered the dinner special: halibut topped with wild mushroom sauce, served with roasted potatoes, carrots, green beans and cauliflower!   Delicious.  Wonderful service and warm ambiance.

We have been here twice, and each time was wonderful. This most recent time around, we got the seafood tower. It had, hands down, the best lobster that I have ever tasted *and* the best baked oysters that I have ever tasted. They must magick their seafood down from some wonderful place on high where the fish are personally blessed by a great deity. Seriously, it was that good. The service was outstanding as well. When we went pre-pandemic, we didnt have reservations because we were just dropping in to check it out, and the service at the bar was superlative. This time, we reserved a table and it was again excellent. They were even nice enough to help me with a mask when Id lost mine after taking it off for dinner. Well be making the trip up again in a couple months to eat here, and Id imagine that as long as we live in the region, well make sure to come by at least two or three times a year if not more.

Highly recommended! We stopped at this stunning restaurant and made a quick reservation and to our surprise we got in. You must have proof of vaccination. Back to the food, we were absolutely blown away. We ordered two ceasers, baked oysters, Salmon wellington, and lobster Mac and cheese, everything was very pleasing to the palate . We will definitely be coming back
Had a amazing dinner here, had the Sockeye Salmon Wellington.

Great dinner out. Everyone in our group really liked their meal. We did make a rezo for 5:30 which was good as they were pretty busy with happy hour. Oysters, appies and drinks on special. Our server was delightful and calm through all the noise (babies crying etc) and busyness. We really liked the oysters, as well as the octopus and paella. Parking: Also right where a bus stop is, so if taking the bus its an easy location to get to.

Been coming to fishworks since 2016, recently came here with my girlfriend for our anniversary and had a wonderful meal. The prawn carbonara and the Hokkaido scollops were delicious. The service however is what stood out to me and my partner, our server Michael was very attentive and helpful with all of our requests and questions. My water was never empty and we felt very well taken care of.

One of my favorite seafood restaurants in Vancouver. For the quality, I think the prices are on the reasonable side given Metro Vancouver. The seafood is fresh, and Ill recommend the starter platter (the King crab is the only thing I think may be previously frozen). The paella is packed with seafood. The salmon Wellington is their signature, but I find it is on the dry side and really needs the pesto sauce to help it out. No fuss good food restaurant to enjoy with your friends and family.
A hidden gem in North Van!! The food was fresh and delicious, and all at a great price point. Will certainly be a go to place!

We live on Vancouver Island and had not been back to this restaurant in about 7 years. Would it still live up to our memories of fantastic food?  OH YES!!! We started with Crispy Squid and Prawns - sooooo good. My hubby had the same as last time - Wild Pacific Halibut Poutine with goat cheese gravy... as good as he remembered. I had the Hokkaido Scallops with home made squash tortellini,  sage burn butter sauce, toasted walnuts. The scallops were cooked to perfection and everything else on the plate was wonderful too. If I could have licked the plate clean, I would have. Also the wine recommendation was spot on. We had a California white called Lieu Dit from the Santa Maria Valley. We highly recommend this restaurant... the staff are professional and friendly. If you are staying in downtown Vancouver hop on the seabuss (route 1 to get there and route 2 to return) and walk to this neighbour gem in North Vancouver. It is soooo good! Thanks Fish Works for a memorable meal.
Just squeaked in before 6 and got a few Happy Hour appies. Seafood Tower was excellent. Friendly server and great service and tasty food. All you can ask for.
Dined a couple weeks ago and had a great experience! The salmon Wellington was superb. Maia was a kind and caring waitress. 10/10!

Came here with the intention of trying their dine out Vancouver 2022 menu but their a la carte menu captured our interest. The price is also very economical for a seafood restaurant. Scallops on the risotto was perfectly cooked and the amount of lobster meat on the lobster Mac and cheese was plentiful. The favourite of the night was the paella. Everything was fresh and delicious. Highly recommend!

What a great experience. I live on the North Shore but first time coming here. Wow I will be back. Very telling when the restaurant is packed and it is a few days after New Years. Service was exceptional and the decor and layout was very welcoming. The food was excellent. We shared the best salad which was huge and then I had the Salmon Wellington, so delicious. My partner had the Sablefish special which she really enjoyed. Suffice it to say we were very full after that dinner. Looking forward to going back.

Fishworks is an excellent seafood restaurant, and its only a matter of time until I go back.  It can get pretty busy. My friends, wife and I were lucky to get a seat at the bar as walk-ins after being turned away from 2 other restaurants.  Service was friendly.  The frontman behind the bar was a true gentleman.  Their wine selection is pretty good but I opted for a beer since we walked in at the end of happy hour. Shucked oysters at happy hour seem like good value for money, so we got some and were served by the frontman. Great way to start the evening. My wife got the lobster bisque. As others have reported, it is really friggin good.  Their salmon wellington is quite simply the best piece of seafood Ive ever had in North Van. Awesome experience.

I started going to fishworks on my visits to N. Vancouver and now, 3 years later I ve relocated here and I m still going and have never been let down with every dish I ve had. My favourite go-to. Service is excellent and staff is friendly, knowledgeable and on top of everything. Highly recommend!

Its one of my favorite seafood restaurants.   Amazing food and spectacular service.  Michal and Tom do a great job behind the bar and the serving folks are amazing.  Attentive Receptive and helpful!  Can not recommend this place enough
it was so delicious; my family enjoyed so much. Especially, the white wine was so good with food.
I had an amazing experience! The food and customer service was off the charts. I will definitely be back when I am in town. Also, Tom was amazing. Made me feel right at home :)
Nice food, tase is good, abbot on pricy side but the it should be ;) Soup is amazing, both of them as we shared as family. There is a Syria s at the end, happy end ;)

Great food! We got the salmon and poutine for dinner and their take on the poutine and salmon Wellington was mouth watering ! Not too pricey either for the food! The customer service was excellent as well.

Greatest place ever. Even my kids (ages 10-14) loved it! Best food at the Shipyard area hands down and worth the walk away from the water. Loved the additional dessert treat. Thank you. Kid-friendliness: Kid friendly for ages 10 and up

I don t know how this place doesn t have 5 stars! Superb food. Best service I ve ever had. So happy I stumbled into this place, best meal on my visit to Vancouver (and this was the only place I hadn t specifically researched trying to find some of the best food!)
I rarely dine in North Van and glad to have found this gem.  Every single dish was so tasty and fresh  nice atmosphere as well
I liked how they served us free sweets after dinner. Ganache tasted really good. Great customer service and delicious and well presented food!

Fishworks is a real CATCH! Never disappoints! The Halibut Poutine is my personal fave but the Salmon Wellington is a close second. Chef extraordinaire always cooks the fish to perfection! 100%!!! Great atmosphere for date night or hosting big parties. Absolutely my favourite place to bring out-of-town visitors to WOW! them. Located in the heart of Lower Lonsdale steps away from the Shipyards. My husband and I feel lucky to live nearby and are truly welcomed and remembered by staff every visit. Fantastic Happy Hour to boot! Best to reserve ahead especially on busy weekends. What a gem!

I love this restaurant and the waiter that helped me the day that I was there. I was really really enjoying my perfectly made BBQ prawn alla carbonara, then whithin a few seconds, the heatstroke hit me so bad that I almost fainted, the guy helped me with a cold towel and water, I left when I was a bit better, but didnt have a chance to tell them that I am so sorry   and thank you for your help   I will come back again for sure.

Excellent choice for a birthday dinner! Lively (a bit noisy) atmosphere, good service and delicious, well presented food.  Our table split a halibut ceviche to start and had Fishworks Paella, Sockeye Salmon Wellington and West Coast Lingcod as mains. All were served in generous portions. Finished off with Creme Brulee to share.  The salmon and creme brulee were the stars of the show. Hope to return soon. Parking: Tough to find parking in LoLo.  We parked at the IGA garage on Esplanade. Wheelchair accessibility: The  main seating area is up a set of 3 stairs. There is one table by the door that is wheelchair accessible.  I have a walker and staff assisted in storing it away from traffic.

Excellent service and perfect food every time we visit. Bought a bottle of wine and something didnt taste quite right, they swapped it out for another with no questions asked. Service is miles above the rest.

This is my favorite North Van restaurant! The food is always so fresh and delicious, and they have a great array of seafood dishes to suit whatever mood you are in. My personal favorites are the Salmon Wellington and the Fish and Chips. Definitely worth stopping by for dinner!
The farmed sturgeon was delicious. They offer a nice selection of dishes. We sat on the patio which was a little loud as it was beside the road. Overall we loved it.

The halibut poutine was delicious! It was my husband s birthday and they offered up chocolate truffles on a Happy Birthday plate - very  sweet. Lucy our server was pleasant, professional and very kind. We definitely will be back. Thank you Lucy!
Best food and coffee in the north shore. Everything is amazing check out the pics. Food

They seated us promptly and were attentive but not overbearing throughout our dinner. Great menu options with generous portion sizes and good prices for what you get. Servers were very friendly and atmosphere was cool. Definitely plan to go back!
Amazing service!  Thank you Chloe for being such an incredible server and making our birthday celebration extra  special. The food and beverages were delicious.

In town from the states (Atlanta, GA) and this place is really nice. Not an expert but I would say more upscale based on what s around it. My wife and I both choose the Halibut (two different versions) and our daughter had the clams and pasta. Also had the salmon carpaccio and the lobster bisque. Don t judge we were hungry. In any case really really good. We were slightly underdressed but didn t feel out of place. Come here, service and food were special!

Our waiter was so friendly and funny. We ordered the paella and the halibut poutine. The portions were more than enough for one person, especially the paella. Both dishes were absolutely delicious and so fresh. The waiter was also great at accommodating peanut/nut allergies.

Glad that we have such a nice seafood restaurant like this in NVan. Every single dish was delicious and oysters were very fresh. Indoor dining area was properly sanitized with proper the social distancing measures.
Popped in for a quick dinner and we were pleasantly surprised to find that Fishworks is excellent in every way. We will definitely be back.

Simply divine. A must try and repeat. The Halibut poutine will simply take you to a new level of poutine tasting that you wish to repeat and repeat. The Creme brulee reminded me my Grammy Easter special threat that I wished to tasted it slowly.
Great food even greater pasta.

Amazing experience. Food wad was more than spectacular and the atmosphere was amazing. The servers along with the rest of the front of house staff were incredibly accommodating. When you re in North Vancouver, THIS is the place to go.
Delicious! Seafood tower for two was perfectly proportioned and the baked oysters were the best. Lobster pasta was full of chunky lobster.
Amazing salmon & paella... quick fresh food with great service! Wouldve been a straight 5 stars if the AC worked. .
Food is great! Definitely one of our favourite restaurants now! Looking forward to try all their delicious food!
I would highly recommend it if you are looking for fresh foods and happy hour in North Vancouver, you will never go wrong with them, staff always friendly and sweet <3

Amazing seafood place and always one of my favourites! I had the Lingcod dish recently and it was very tasty and refreshing. The vegetable was crisp and the fish was cooked perfectly. The Paella and the Salmon Wellington are amazing too. I discovered that taking SeaBus from Waterfront Station is so much faster and easier. Its a must 10-12 minutes scenic ferry ride and you get to enjoy an amazing view of the mountains and Vancouver skyscrapers. The restaurant is only a block from the Quay Market.
Ate here the other night and the service was outstanding! My server, Savannah, made my experience. I couldn t recommend this place enough!
We went for the dine out menu. Everything is so delicious and service is excellent. We also ordered some drinks and oysters.
Excellent seafood very friendly and nice service. Prices are fair for the quality of food and location. Highly recommend. Parking: Public parking available near the location.

Hip atmosphere. Delicious food. I had the clam chowder, a caesar salad and a pint of locally brewed ginger beer - loved it all. Sat at the bar and conversed with a thoughtful Swiss architect - also out for dinner in his own. It was a lovely evening.
Great north van gem. The seafood paella was so good!!

Really impressed at how good the food was! Recently Ive been to two other fancy seafood restaurants on the north shore and fishworks was the best. The others werent bad but wishworks is just a step above with flavor and quality.

I visit Fishworks every time that Im in North Vancouver, more than once per year, because the food, ambiance and service is always excellent. For the first time I sat at the bar; what a wonderful experience! To note that Tom is just the man behind the bar or the barman totally misses the point. Tom is the maestro food & entertainment director, he greets as many as he can, brings you into his dining area while ensuring that the entire restaurant is running like the well oiled machine that it is. So whether its a quiet tete-a-tete, a boisterous gathering or simply oysters and a beer you must visit Fishworks and say hi to Tom to be entertained, fulfilled and satisfied.
Good oysters (2.5$ ea from vancouver island) huge and mild salty Pasta is steelhead garganelli - fresh creamy mildly sour nice flavours Wine Pinot Gris rich spicy and sweet paired well with the food
Delicious Dinner.  Good service, friendly, efficient. Very noisy. Vegetarian options: The only vegetarian item I saw on the menu was a green salad. No main course.
We had a fabulous dinner. We would definitely recommend the raw oysters, the lemongrass, coconut mussels and the squash ravioli with scallops, delicious! Cant wait to go back! Food
Some of best seafood/dinner menu and very well equipped staff. While it can be a bit cramped and hot on certain days, it is 100% overshadowed by the fantastic menu and staff.

***DROOL*** When looking into Fishworks before our arrival, there were so many posts about the Salmon Wellington that everyone at my table ended up ordering it. It was absolutely divine. The same can be said about the squid and prawn appetizer and the chocolate mousse dessert. Im looking forward to visiting again and trying more menu items--Im confident theyll be equally delicious.
We had a wonderful dinner! Delightful service and a fantastic meal to wrap up our getaway. Well definitely be back!
Amazing food, wonderful service. Definetely coming back!

Delicious dinner with swift service and super friendly staff. Our food tasted amazing and fresh - from clam chowder to salmon and halibut. Our kids really enjoyed lobster mac&cheese Even dessert cream brulee was mouthwatering

Absolutely fantastic atmosphere and food. Get a reservation cuz this place is popular. Happy hour oysters at the bar, muscles in a garlic broth, and an entertaining bartender shucking and making drinks. Give this place a go if that sounds like your thing.

Delicious food. We did the dine out vancouver menu. Everything was really delicious. Service was great. The only bad thing Id say is that some (or maybe just this one) of the entrees are very minimal and we didnt know that they didnt come with a side, we would have ordered a side had we known and then didnt want to wait for a side with the dinner already having been served - my husband left feeling a little hungry. Otherwise, everything was amazing. Would def recommend.
Food is consistently good. Prices are reasonable, and portions are filling.
Yummy!! Came here for fish and it was delicious Oysters, main mane and deserts (tiramisu)were great! Highly recommend
Excellent place to have a seafood dishes!! Appetizers, Mains, desserts, everything tasted wonderful!!
highly recommend this restaurant for a drink and appetizers. The staff are incredible even during busy hours.

I can t say enough about how perfect every element of my dining experience was. Food, wine, service, perfect. I have been here many times and it is consistently exceptional. This time sharing with my sister, just now cancer free and able to be out of the house for the first time in two years. Where to go?  No question, Fishworks, and it did not disappoint.  Thank you all of you.
Lovely evening, good food on Lonsdale.
Excellent food, presentation, service, ambiance. If you love seafood, you really have to visit - its our go to place, always reliable and delicious.
Back after a long break and glad we did. The good and service were great. Loved the crispy prawns and squid!

Tried dinner at Fishworks for Dineout Vancouver 2023. The staff was able to accommodate for a wheelchair and the service was excellent. That said, there was no warm-bread and we were seated right by the door. Table favourites were octopus, scallops, and the poached-pear dessert. Steamed whole fish and other fish dinner was also well-prepared, tasty, and worth a try. Reasonable pricing, good food, highlighted by superior service earned Fishworks this 5-star review. Parking: No parking in front, but side streets and lot parking available Wheelchair accessibility: Able to accommodate, call ahead to confirm!
Really good food. Was there for a private function and the wait staff performed their jobs very well.

Make a reservation so as not to be disappointed at the door - as Fishworks is a local fave and well worth it! Top notch service and perfectly prepared dishes. I had the crab cakes appie and it was delicious - not over cooked at all. Scallops are a personal favourite so I went with the risotto and it was perfection. Great selection of BC and international wines. A local gem!

The best seafood in North Vancouver hands down. Great bartender, oysters, crab and scallops. The Sablefish was amazing as well. This little hidden gem was packed and for good reason. Make reservations, you will need them!

Been here twice and had a lovely experience both times. We ve had the crab cakes, salmon Wellington and halibut poutine. We thought the menu included original options, our server was very friendly, and the food was very tasty. We had nice, pairing wines as well. Will definitely go back again!

Excellent food. Reasonable prices.  Street parking nearby.  Usually crowded even on weeknights.  Check out TheTower a sampler designed for two (or 3 on a diet). Great attentive staff.  They also serve great fish and chips.
